					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12856441#post-4640902</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12856441/scp-4457#post-4640902</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 10 May 2020 16:26:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>glewmie</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3448977</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hello and thank you for the +1 and reading the story.</p> <p>We decided to go with symbiotic because, while the process is transformative for the host, it's otherwise &quot;harmless&quot;. It isn't exactly parasitism because resources are shared freely between the host and the isopod.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12856441#post-4639964</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12856441/scp-4457#post-4639964</link>
				<description></description>
